<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="985" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d985">
                    <head>Captain Gloor</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation]</note>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Schöftland</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p rend="flushleft">
                        <hi rend="italic">The Editor of the Bund, in Berne:</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit to you the lists
                        of the signatures of the Feldschützen and Leist-Gesellschaft of this place
                        to the general address of sympathy <pb facs="0667" n="595" xml:id="pg_595"/>
                        and condolence to the North American Union, and its inhabitants, our
                        brothers beyond the ocean, on the occasion of the assassination of the
                        martyr President, Abraham Lincoln, and for their recent glorious victories
                        over the southern rebels. You will please have them sent to the proper
                        address, and oblige the undersigned.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>T. GLOOR, </signed>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>